
[1]separate

   SEP'ARATE, v. t. [L. separo.]

   1. To disunite; to divide; to sever; to part, in almost any manner,
   either things naturally or casually joined. The parts of a solid
   substance may be separated by breaking, cutting or splitting, or by
   fusion, decomposition or natural dissolution. A compound body may be
   separated into its constituent parts. Friends may be separated by
   necessity, and must be separated by death. The prism separates the
   several kinds of colored rays. A riddle separates the chaff from the
   grain.

   2. To set apart from a number for a particular service.
